    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in the Soviet Union (
                        Harriman
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v04</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d398</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">398</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-11-19T18:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-11-19T18:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-19T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="398" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">874.00/11–2045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-20T02:00:00+03:00">November 20, 1945—2 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3904. There follows translation of pertinent part of Vyshinski’s letter of
                    November 19 acknowledging my letter informing him of the message which Barnes
                    handed the Bulgarian Govt regarding the Bulgarian elections. <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Deem it advisable to remark that the Soviet Govt does not share the
                            evaluation contained in your letter of the political situation in
                            Bulgaria and cannot agree with the statement concerning the absence in
                            Bulgaria at the present time of satisfactory conditions for the carrying
                            of free elections to the National Assembly.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>To the Dept 3904, repeated to Sofia 133, London 587.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
